Why would one use Pandas rather than the standard data manipulation features provided by NumPy?
      
      Pandas is a Data manipulation using Pandas is more straightforward. With the tabluar data with rows and columns, Pandas, which 
      is column-oriented data analysis API, can handle the input data better. Also, most of the data manupulating and analysing features
      provided are comprehensive.
      
Under what circumstances would it be useful to reorder/shuffle a Pandas DataFrame?
    
      It would be useful to reorder/shuffle a Pandas DataFrams to sanitize the input by allowing "missign" indices. 
      
